<h1>Fanorona</h1>

<hr>
<p><applet code="Fanorona.class" archive="Fanorona.zip" width="500"
height="350">
<div align="center"><img src="applet.jpg" width="496" height="347"
alt="Fanorona applet screenshot"><br>
<small>If you were running Java, you'd see a nice game-playing
applet instead of this screenshot.</small></div>
</applet></p>

<hr>
<p>I wrote this after the fact as a demo for my <a href="../../">
class on board game programming</a>. A <a href="Fanorona.hqx">
standalone Macintosh application version</a> and the <a href= 
"source/">source code</a> are also available.</p>

<p></p>

<p>Here's <a href= 
"http://rescomp.stanford.edu/~domingo2/stuff/fanorona.html">another
Java Fanorona game</a> (without computer-play features), <a href= 
"http://www.thibault.org/fanorona/">Fanorona for GNOME</a>, a <a
href="http://eiss.erols.com/pbmserv/fanorona.html">play-by-email
server</a>, <a href= 
"http://members.aol.com/wgreview/fanorona.html">a description
of the game from the Knights of the Square Table</a>,
<a href="http://utenti.tripod.it/necronomicon/giochi/fanorona.htm">another
description of the game (in Italiano)</a>,
and
<a href="http://hala.refer.mg/concours/4/quotidi.html">a
web site from Madagascar (in French)</a>.</p>

